  "body": "# Problem\r\n\r\nFunctions `quo2.foundations.colors/theme-alpha` and `quo2.foundations.colors/custom-color-by-theme` are not *contextually themeable*, which means they rely exclusively on the global state `quo2.theme/theme-state`.\r\n\r\nThis means these functions can't be used with the React context `quo2.theme/theme-context`, which is our current approach to make Quo truly themeable.\r\n\r\n## Implementation\r\n\r\nGiven our goal is to make the Quo library fully themeable, we should update such functions and their usages to accept a `theme` argument.\r\n\r\nYou may prefer to open more than one PR to solve this issue because there may be too many function calls to update.",
